 <info>
  <link type="guide" xref="index#setup"/>
  <desc>Setup remote backup on a network share</desc>
 </info>
 <title>Network Share</title>
 <p><app>Pika Backup</app> supports backing up on network shares.</p>
 <note style="tip">
  <p>Installing BorgBackup on the server and <link xref="setup-remote">using SSH</link> can significantly improve performance.</p>
 </note>
 <steps>
  <item>
   <p>Select the <gui>Setup Backup</gui> button.</p>
   <media type="image" src="media/setup-button.svg"/>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Select <gui>Create New Repository</gui> or <gui>Use Existing Repository</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Perform one of the following</p>
   <list>
    <item>
     <p>Connect to the network share using <app>GNOME Files</app></p>
     <list>
      <item>
       <p>See <link href="help:gnome-help/nautilus-connect">GNOME Files</link> help pages for reference</p>
      </item>
      <item>
       <p>The network share will show up in the setup dialog automatically</p>
      </item>
      <item>
       <p>Choose the network share</p>
      </item>
      <item>
       <p>Ensure the <gui>Repository Folder</gui> has the network share selected. The <gui style="button">Repository Folder</gui> row can be used to select a sub-folder on the network share.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
       <p>The new backup <link xref="general-glossary#repository">repository</link> will be created in a folder with the specified <gui>Repository Name</gui>.</p>
      </item>
     </list>
    </item>
    <item>
     <p>Select <gui>Remote Location</gui></p>
     <list>
      <item>
       <p>Enter a <app>GNOME Files</app> compatible URI. SMB or SFTP are recommended.</p>
       <note style="tip">
        <p>It is possible to drop network folders from <app>GNOME Files</app> on the input field.</p>
       </note>
       <note style="advanced">
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <p>Server addresses are made up of a protocol prefix and an address. Examples:</p>
        <p><code>smb://user@server.example.org:port/share/path/to/backup</code> - Samba</p>
        <p><code>sftp://user@server.example.org:port/path/to/backup</code> - SFTP</p>
       </note>
      </item>
      <item>
       <p>The new backup <link xref="general-glossary#repository">repository</link> will be created at the URI location. Ensure the folder is empty.</p>
      </item>
     </list>
    </item>
   </list>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Press <gui style="button">Continue</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Choose the desired <link xref="general-glossary#encryption">encryption</link> settings</p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Press <gui style="button">Create</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Configure the <gui>Files to Back Up</gui> and <gui>Exclude from Backup</gui> sections</p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Press <gui style="button">Back Up Now</gui></p>
  </item>
 </steps>
</page>
